<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>Mockingbird - Mock your data (BETA)</title>
        <meta httpEquiv='X-UA-Compatible' content='IE=edge'>
        <meta name='viewport" content="initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=0'>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="{context_root}/bower_components/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css"/>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="{context_root}/public/css/style.css"/>
        <script type="text/javascript" src="{context_root}/public/js/vendor.js"></script>
    </head>
    <body>
        <nav class="x1-ui-top-navigation navbar navbar-inverse navbar-fixed-top" role="navigation">
            <div class="container-fluid">
                <div class="navbar-header">
                    <a class="navbar-brand" href="{context_root}/">
                        Mockingbird | Mock-up your data
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </nav>
        <div class="content">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-12">
                        <h1>
                            Quickly Mock up an API Endpoint
                        </h1>
                        <hr/>
                        <p>
                            Mockingbird allows you to create a mock API Endpoint, assign Verbs (GET|POST|PUT|PATCH|DELETE), and assign response codes and JSON data to each of those verbs.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Mock Endpoints can support multiple verbs, each can have their own response code and data.
                        </p>
                        <hr/>
                        <p>
                            <a href="{context_root}/mocks" style="margin-right: 10px;">
                                <button class="btn btn-success">View Endpoints</button>
                            </a>
                            <a href="{context_root}/mocks/create">
                                <button class="btn btn-primary">Create an Endpoint</button>
                            </a>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>
